==Finnish==

===Etymology===
From ''[[yhdys-]]'' eg. "united, uniting" (''in compounds'') + the plural of ''[[valta]]'' "power; country (''in compounds'', see ''[[Itävalta]]'')", whence also ''[[valtio]]'' "state, country".

===Proper noun===
'''Yhdysvallat''' ''plural'' (''genitive often'' '''Yhdysvaltain''' ''and not the "modern" form'' '''Yhdysvaltojen''')

# the [[United States]].

